12/// !!! NOTE !!! These tests happily avoid overflow cases & out-of-range arguments
13/// so that output arrays contain neigher Inf's nor Nan's.
14/// Handling such cases would require special modification of check function
15/// (validate_test_results) => TBD.
16/// Also, need some logarithmic-scale generation of input data. Right now it is done (in some tests)
17/// by generating min/max boundaries for random data in logarimithic scale, but
18/// within the same test case all the input array elements are of the same order.
19
20class Core_MathTest : public cvtest::ArrayTest
21{
22public:
23 typedef cvtest::ArrayTest Base;
24 Core_MathTest();
25protected:
26 void get_test_array_types_and_sizes( int test_case_idx, vector<vector<Size> >& sizes,
27 vector<vector<int> >& types);
28 double get_success_error_level( int /*test_case_idx*/, int i, int j );
29 bool test_nd;
30};
31

33Core_MathTest::Core_MathTest()

35 optional_mask = false;
36
37 test_array[INPUT].push_back(NULL);
38 test_array[OUTPUT].push_back(NULL);
39 test_array[REF_OUTPUT].push_back(NULL);
40
41 test_nd = false;
42}

45double Core_MathTest::get_success_error_level( int /*test_case_idx*/, int i, int j )
46{
47 return test_mat[i][j].depth() == CV_32F ? FLT_EPSILON*128 : DBL_EPSILON*1024;
48}

51void Core_MathTest::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( int test_case_idx,
52 vector<vector<Size> >& sizes,
53 vector<vector<int> >& types)
54{
55 RNG& rng = ts->get_rng();
56 int depth = cvtest::randInt(rng)%2 + CV_32F;
57 int cn = cvtest::randInt(rng) % 4 + 1, type = CV_MAKETYPE(depth, cn);
58 size_t i, j;
59 Base::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( test_case_idx, sizes, types );
60
61 for( i = 0; i < test_array.size(); i++ )
62 {
63 size_t count = test_array[i].size();
64 for( j = 0; j < count; j++ )
65 types[i][j] = type;
66 }
67 test_nd = cvtest::randInt(rng)%3 == 0;
68}

75public:
76 typedef Core_MathTest Base;

90Core_PowTest::Core_PowTest()

95
96void Core_PowTest::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( int test_case_idx,
97 vector<vector<Size> >& sizes,
98 vector<vector<int> >& types )
99{
100 RNG& rng = ts->get_rng();
101 int depth = cvtest::randInt(rng) % (CV_64F+1);
102 int cn = cvtest::randInt(rng) % 4 + 1;
103 size_t i, j;
104 Base::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( test_case_idx, sizes, types );
105 depth += depth == CV_8S;
106
107 if( depth < CV_32F || cvtest::randInt(rng)%8 == 0 )
108 // integer power
109 power = (int)(cvtest::randInt(rng)%21 - 10);
110 else
111 {
112 i = cvtest::randInt(rng)%17;
113 power = i == 16 ? 1./3 : i == 15 ? 0.5 : i == 14 ? -0.5 : cvtest::randReal(rng)*10 - 5;
114 }
115
116 for( i = 0; i < test_array.size(); i++ )
117 {
118 size_t count = test_array[i].size();
119 int type = CV_MAKETYPE(depth, cn);
120 for( j = 0; j < count; j++ )
121 types[i][j] = type;
122 }
123 test_nd = cvtest::randInt(rng)%3 == 0;
124}
125
126
127double Core_PowTest::get_success_error_level( int test_case_idx, int i, int j )
128{
129 int depth = test_mat[i][j].depth();
130 if( depth < CV_32F )
131 return power == cvRound(power) && power >= 0 ? 0 : 1;
132 else
133 return Base::get_success_error_level( test_case_idx, i, j );
134}

136
137void Core_PowTest::get_minmax_bounds( int /*i*/, int /*j*/, int type, Scalar& low, Scalar& high )
138{
139 double l, u = cvtest::randInt(ts->get_rng())%1000 + 1;
140 if( power > 0 )
141 {
142 double mval = cvtest::getMaxVal(type);
143 double u1 = pow(mval,1./power)*2;
144 u = MIN(u,u1);
145 }
146
147 l = power == cvRound(power) ? -u : FLT_EPSILON;
148 low = Scalar::all(l);
149 high = Scalar::all(u);
150}
151
152
153void Core_PowTest::run_func()
154{
155 if(!test_nd)
156 {
157 if( fabs(power-1./3) <= DBL_EPSILON && test_mat[INPUT][0].depth() == CV_32F )
158 {
159 Mat a = test_mat[INPUT][0], b = test_mat[OUTPUT][0];
160
161 a = a.reshape(1);
162 b = b.reshape(1);
163 for( int i = 0; i < a.rows; i++ )
164 {
165 b.at<float>(i,0) = (float)fabs(cvCbrt(a.at<float>(i,0)));
166 for( int j = 1; j < a.cols; j++ )
167 b.at<float>(i,j) = (float)fabs(cv::cubeRoot(a.at<float>(i,j)));
168 }
169 }
170 else
171 cvPow( test_array[INPUT][0], test_array[OUTPUT][0], power );
172 }
173 else
174 {
175 Mat& a = test_mat[INPUT][0];
176 Mat& b = test_mat[OUTPUT][0];
177 if(power == 0.5)
178 cv::sqrt(a, b);
179 else
180 cv::pow(a, power, b);
181 }
182}
183
184
185inline static int ipow( int a, int power )
186{
187 int b = 1;
188 while( power > 0 )
189 {
190 if( power&1 )
191 b *= a, power--;
192 else
193 a *= a, power >>= 1;
194 }
195 return b;
196}
197
198
199inline static double ipow( double a, int power )
200{
201 double b = 1.;
202 while( power > 0 )
203 {
204 if( power&1 )
205 b *= a, power--;
206 else
207 a *= a, power >>= 1;
208 }
209 return b;
210}

212
213void Core_PowTest::prepare_to_validation( int /*test_case_idx*/ )
214{
215 const Mat& a = test_mat[INPUT][0];
216 Mat& b = test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0];
217
218 int depth = a.depth();
219 int ncols = a.cols*a.channels();
220 int ipower = cvRound(power), apower = abs(ipower);
221 int i, j;
222
223 for( i = 0; i < a.rows; i++ )
224 {
225 const uchar* a_data = a.ptr(i);
226 uchar* b_data = b.ptr(i);
227
228 switch( depth )
229 {
230 case CV_8U:
231 if( ipower < 0 )
232 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
233 {
234 int val = ((uchar*)a_data)[j];
235 ((uchar*)b_data)[j] = (uchar)(val <= 1 ? val :
236 val == 2 && ipower == -1 ? 1 : 0);
237 }
238 else
239 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
240 {
241 int val = ((uchar*)a_data)[j];
242 val = ipow( val, ipower );
243 ((uchar*)b_data)[j] = saturate_cast<uchar>(val);
244 }
245 break;
246 case CV_8S:
247 if( ipower < 0 )
248 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
249 {
250 int val = ((char*)a_data)[j];
251 ((char*)b_data)[j] = (char)((val&~1)==0 ? val :
252 val ==-1 ? 1-2*(ipower&1) :
253 val == 2 && ipower == -1 ? 1 : 0);
254 }
255 else
256 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
257 {
258 int val = ((char*)a_data)[j];
259 val = ipow( val, ipower );
260 ((char*)b_data)[j] = saturate_cast<schar>(val);
261 }
262 break;
263 case CV_16U:
264 if( ipower < 0 )
265 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
266 {
267 int val = ((ushort*)a_data)[j];
268 ((ushort*)b_data)[j] = (ushort)((val&~1)==0 ? val :
269 val ==-1 ? 1-2*(ipower&1) :
270 val == 2 && ipower == -1 ? 1 : 0);
271 }
272 else
273 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
274 {
275 int val = ((ushort*)a_data)[j];
276 val = ipow( val, ipower );
277 ((ushort*)b_data)[j] = saturate_cast<ushort>(val);
278 }
279 break;
280 case CV_16S:
281 if( ipower < 0 )
282 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
283 {
284 int val = ((short*)a_data)[j];
285 ((short*)b_data)[j] = (short)((val&~1)==0 ? val :
286 val ==-1 ? 1-2*(ipower&1) :
287 val == 2 && ipower == -1 ? 1 : 0);
288 }
289 else
290 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
291 {
292 int val = ((short*)a_data)[j];
293 val = ipow( val, ipower );
294 ((short*)b_data)[j] = saturate_cast<short>(val);
295 }
296 break;
297 case CV_32S:
298 if( ipower < 0 )
299 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
300 {
301 int val = ((int*)a_data)[j];
302 ((int*)b_data)[j] = (val&~1)==0 ? val :
303 val ==-1 ? 1-2*(ipower&1) :
304 val == 2 && ipower == -1 ? 1 : 0;
305 }
306 else
307 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
308 {
309 int val = ((int*)a_data)[j];
310 val = ipow( val, ipower );
311 ((int*)b_data)[j] = val;
312 }
313 break;
314 case CV_32F:
315 if( power != ipower )
316 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
317 {
318 double val = ((float*)a_data)[j];
319 val = pow( fabs(val), power );
320 ((float*)b_data)[j] = (float)val;
321 }
322 else
323 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
324 {
325 double val = ((float*)a_data)[j];
326 if( ipower < 0 )
327 val = 1./val;
328 val = ipow( val, apower );
329 ((float*)b_data)[j] = (float)val;
330 }
331 break;
332 case CV_64F:
333 if( power != ipower )
334 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
335 {
336 double val = ((double*)a_data)[j];
337 val = pow( fabs(val), power );
338 ((double*)b_data)[j] = (double)val;
339 }
340 else
341 for( j = 0; j < ncols; j++ )
342 {
343 double val = ((double*)a_data)[j];
344 if( ipower < 0 )
345 val = 1./val;
346 val = ipow( val, apower );
347 ((double*)b_data)[j] = (double)val;
348 }
349 break;
350 }
351 }
352}

358class Core_MatrixTest : public cvtest::ArrayTest
359{
360public:
361 typedef cvtest::ArrayTest Base;
362 Core_MatrixTest( int in_count, int out_count,
363 bool allow_int, bool scalar_output, int max_cn );
364protected:
365 void get_test_array_types_and_sizes( int test_case_idx,
366 vector<vector<Size> >& sizes,
367 vector<vector<int> >& types );
368 double get_success_error_level( int test_case_idx, int i, int j );
369 bool allow_int;
370 bool scalar_output;
371 int max_cn;
372};
373
374
375Core_MatrixTest::Core_MatrixTest( int in_count, int out_count,
376 bool _allow_int, bool _scalar_output, int _max_cn )
377: allow_int(_allow_int), scalar_output(_scalar_output), max_cn(_max_cn)
378{
379 int i;
380 for( i = 0; i < in_count; i++ )
381 test_array[INPUT].push_back(NULL);
382
383 for( i = 0; i < out_count; i++ )
384 {
385 test_array[OUTPUT].push_back(NULL);
386 test_array[REF_OUTPUT].push_back(NULL);
387 }
388
389 element_wise_relative_error = false;
390}
391
392
393void Core_MatrixTest::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( int test_case_idx,
394 vector<vector<Size> >& sizes,
395 vector<vector<int> >& types )
396{
397 RNG& rng = ts->get_rng();
398 int depth = cvtest::randInt(rng) % (allow_int ? CV_64F+1 : 2);
399 int cn = cvtest::randInt(rng) % max_cn + 1;
400 size_t i, j;
401
402 if( allow_int )
403 depth += depth == CV_8S;
404 else
405 depth += CV_32F;
406
407 Base::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( test_case_idx, sizes, types );
408
409 for( i = 0; i < test_array.size(); i++ )
410 {
411 size_t count = test_array[i].size();
412 int flag = (i == OUTPUT || i == REF_OUTPUT) && scalar_output;
413 int type = !flag ? CV_MAKETYPE(depth, cn) : CV_64FC1;
414
415 for( j = 0; j < count; j++ )
416 {
417 types[i][j] = type;
418 if( flag )
419 sizes[i][j] = Size( 4, 1 );
420 }
421 }
422}
423
424
425double Core_MatrixTest::get_success_error_level( int test_case_idx, int i, int j )
426{
427 int input_depth = test_mat[INPUT][0].depth();
428 double input_precision = input_depth < CV_32F ? 0 : input_depth == CV_32F ? 5e-5 : 5e-10;
429 double output_precision = Base::get_success_error_level( test_case_idx, i, j );
430 return MAX(input_precision, output_precision);
431}

456
457void Core_TraceTest::prepare_to_validation( int )
458{
459 Mat& mat = test_mat[INPUT][0];
460 int count = MIN( mat.rows, mat.cols );
461 Mat diag(count, 1, mat.type(), mat.data, mat.step + mat.elemSize());
462 Scalar r = cvtest::mean(diag);
463 r *= (double)count;
464
465 test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0].at<Scalar>(0,0) = r;
466}

518void Core_CrossProductTest::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( int,
519 vector<vector<Size> >& sizes,
520 vector<vector<int> >& types )
521{
522 RNG& rng = ts->get_rng();
523 int depth = cvtest::randInt(rng) % 2 + CV_32F;
524 int cn = cvtest::randInt(rng) & 1 ? 3 : 1, type = CV_MAKETYPE(depth, cn);
525 CvSize sz;
526
527 types[INPUT][0] = types[INPUT][1] = types[OUTPUT][0] = types[REF_OUTPUT][0] = type;
528
529 if( cn == 3 )
530 sz = Size(1,1);
531 else if( cvtest::randInt(rng) & 1 )
532 sz = Size(3,1);
533 else
534 sz = Size(1,3);
535
536 sizes[INPUT][0] = sizes[INPUT][1] = sizes[OUTPUT][0] = sizes[REF_OUTPUT][0] = sz;
537}

545
546void Core_CrossProductTest::prepare_to_validation( int )
547{
548 CvScalar a = {{0,0,0,0}}, b = {{0,0,0,0}}, c = {{0,0,0,0}};
549
550 if( test_mat[INPUT][0].rows > 1 )
551 {
552 a.val[0] = cvGetReal2D( test_array[INPUT][0], 0, 0 );
553 a.val[1] = cvGetReal2D( test_array[INPUT][0], 1, 0 );
554 a.val[2] = cvGetReal2D( test_array[INPUT][0], 2, 0 );
555
556 b.val[0] = cvGetReal2D( test_array[INPUT][1], 0, 0 );
557 b.val[1] = cvGetReal2D( test_array[INPUT][1], 1, 0 );
558 b.val[2] = cvGetReal2D( test_array[INPUT][1], 2, 0 );
559 }
560 else if( test_mat[INPUT][0].cols > 1 )
561 {
562 a.val[0] = cvGetReal1D( test_array[INPUT][0], 0 );
563 a.val[1] = cvGetReal1D( test_array[INPUT][0], 1 );
564 a.val[2] = cvGetReal1D( test_array[INPUT][0], 2 );
565
566 b.val[0] = cvGetReal1D( test_array[INPUT][1], 0 );
567 b.val[1] = cvGetReal1D( test_array[INPUT][1], 1 );
568 b.val[2] = cvGetReal1D( test_array[INPUT][1], 2 );
569 }
570 else
571 {
572 a = cvGet1D( test_array[INPUT][0], 0 );
573 b = cvGet1D( test_array[INPUT][1], 0 );
574 }
575
576 c.val[2] = a.val[0]*b.val[1] - a.val[1]*b.val[0];
577 c.val[1] = -a.val[0]*b.val[2] + a.val[2]*b.val[0];
578 c.val[0] = a.val[1]*b.val[2] - a.val[2]*b.val[1];
579
580 if( test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0].rows > 1 )
581 {
582 cvSetReal2D( test_array[REF_OUTPUT][0], 0, 0, c.val[0] );
583 cvSetReal2D( test_array[REF_OUTPUT][0], 1, 0, c.val[1] );
584 cvSetReal2D( test_array[REF_OUTPUT][0], 2, 0, c.val[2] );
585 }
586 else if( test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0].cols > 1 )
587 {
588 cvSetReal1D( test_array[REF_OUTPUT][0], 0, c.val[0] );
589 cvSetReal1D( test_array[REF_OUTPUT][0], 1, c.val[1] );
590 cvSetReal1D( test_array[REF_OUTPUT][0], 2, c.val[2] );
591 }
592 else
593 {
594 cvSet1D( test_array[REF_OUTPUT][0], 0, c );
595 }
596}

608 void get_minmax_bounds( int /*i*/, int /*j*/, int /*type*/, Scalar& low, Scalar& high );

611 void prepare_to_validation( int test_case_idx );

613 double alpha, beta;

616Core_GEMMTest::Core_GEMMTest() : Core_MatrixTest( 5, 1, false, false, 2 )
617{
618 test_case_count = 100;
619 max_log_array_size = 10;
620 alpha = beta = 0;
621}
622
623
624void Core_GEMMTest::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( int test_case_idx, vector<vector<Size> >& sizes, vector<vector<int> >& types )
625{
626 RNG& rng = ts->get_rng();
627 Size sizeA;
628 Base::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( test_case_idx, sizes, types );
629 sizeA = sizes[INPUT][0];
630 Base::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( test_case_idx, sizes, types );
631 sizes[INPUT][0] = sizeA;
632 sizes[INPUT][2] = sizes[INPUT][3] = Size(1,1);
633 types[INPUT][2] = types[INPUT][3] &= ~CV_MAT_CN_MASK;
634
635 tabc_flag = cvtest::randInt(rng) & 7;
636
637 switch( tabc_flag & (CV_GEMM_A_T|CV_GEMM_B_T) )
638 {
639 case 0:
640 sizes[INPUT][1].height = sizes[INPUT][0].width;
641 sizes[OUTPUT][0].height = sizes[INPUT][0].height;
642 sizes[OUTPUT][0].width = sizes[INPUT][1].width;
643 break;
644 case CV_GEMM_B_T:
645 sizes[INPUT][1].width = sizes[INPUT][0].width;
646 sizes[OUTPUT][0].height = sizes[INPUT][0].height;
647 sizes[OUTPUT][0].width = sizes[INPUT][1].height;
648 break;
649 case CV_GEMM_A_T:
650 sizes[INPUT][1].height = sizes[INPUT][0].height;
651 sizes[OUTPUT][0].height = sizes[INPUT][0].width;
652 sizes[OUTPUT][0].width = sizes[INPUT][1].width;
653 break;
654 case CV_GEMM_A_T | CV_GEMM_B_T:
655 sizes[INPUT][1].width = sizes[INPUT][0].height;
656 sizes[OUTPUT][0].height = sizes[INPUT][0].width;
657 sizes[OUTPUT][0].width = sizes[INPUT][1].height;
658 break;
659 }
660
661 sizes[REF_OUTPUT][0] = sizes[OUTPUT][0];
662
663 if( cvtest::randInt(rng) & 1 )
664 sizes[INPUT][4] = Size(0,0);
665 else if( !(tabc_flag & CV_GEMM_C_T) )
666 sizes[INPUT][4] = sizes[OUTPUT][0];
667 else
668 {
669 sizes[INPUT][4].width = sizes[OUTPUT][0].height;
670 sizes[INPUT][4].height = sizes[OUTPUT][0].width;
671 }
672}

675int Core_GEMMTest::prepare_test_case( int test_case_idx )
676{
677 int code = Base::prepare_test_case( test_case_idx );
678 if( code > 0 )
679 {
680 alpha = cvGetReal2D( test_array[INPUT][2], 0, 0 );
681 beta = cvGetReal2D( test_array[INPUT][3], 0, 0 );
682 }
683 return code;
684}

693
694void Core_GEMMTest::run_func()

732void Core_MulTransposedTest::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( int test_case_idx, vector<vector<Size> >& sizes, vector<vector<int> >& types )
733{
734 RNG& rng = ts->get_rng();
735 int bits = cvtest::randInt(rng);
736 int src_type = cvtest::randInt(rng) % 5;
737 int dst_type = cvtest::randInt(rng) % 2;
738
739 src_type = src_type == 0 ? CV_8U : src_type == 1 ? CV_16U : src_type == 2 ? CV_16S :
740 src_type == 3 ? CV_32F : CV_64F;
741 dst_type = dst_type == 0 ? CV_32F : CV_64F;

743
744 Core_MatrixTest::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( test_case_idx, sizes, types );
745
746 if( bits & 1 )
747 sizes[INPUT][1] = Size(0,0);
748 else
749 {
750 sizes[INPUT][1] = sizes[INPUT][0];
751 if( bits & 2 )
752 sizes[INPUT][1].height = 1;
753 if( bits & 4 )
754 sizes[INPUT][1].width = 1;
755 }
756
757 sizes[TEMP][0] = sizes[INPUT][0];
758 types[INPUT][0] = src_type;
759 types[OUTPUT][0] = types[REF_OUTPUT][0] = types[INPUT][1] = types[TEMP][0] = dst_type;
760
761 order = (bits & 8) != 0;
762 sizes[OUTPUT][0].width = sizes[OUTPUT][0].height = order == 0 ?
763 sizes[INPUT][0].height : sizes[INPUT][0].width;
764 sizes[REF_OUTPUT][0] = sizes[OUTPUT][0];
765}

782void Core_MulTransposedTest::prepare_to_validation( int )
783{
784 const Mat& src = test_mat[INPUT][0];
785 Mat delta = test_mat[INPUT][1];
786 Mat& temp = test_mat[TEMP][0];
787 if( !delta.empty() )
788 {
789 if( delta.rows < src.rows || delta.cols < src.cols )
790 {
791 cv::repeat( delta, src.rows/delta.rows, src.cols/delta.cols, temp);
792 delta = temp;
793 }
794 cvtest::add( src, 1, delta, -1, Scalar::all(0), temp, temp.type());
795 }
796 else
797 src.convertTo(temp, temp.type());
798
799 cvtest::gemm( temp, temp, 1., Mat(), 0, test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0], order == 0 ? GEMM_2_T : GEMM_1_T );

856 else
857 sizes[INPUT][2] = Size(1,dst_cn);
858 types[INPUT][2] &= ~CV_MAT_CN_MASK;

862 sizes[INPUT][1] = Size(mat_cols,dst_cn);

956
957static void cvTsPerspectiveTransform( const CvArr* _src, CvArr* _dst, const CvMat* transmat )
958{
959 int i, j, cols;
960 int cn, depth, mat_depth;
961 CvMat astub, bstub, *a, *b;
962 double mat[16];
963
964 a = cvGetMat( _src, &astub, 0, 0 );
965 b = cvGetMat( _dst, &bstub, 0, 0 );
966
967 cn = CV_MAT_CN(a->type);
968 depth = CV_MAT_DEPTH(a->type);
969 mat_depth = CV_MAT_DEPTH(transmat->type);
970 cols = transmat->cols;
971
972 // prepare cn x (cn + 1) transform matrix
973 if( mat_depth == CV_32F )
974 {
975 for( i = 0; i < transmat->rows; i++ )
976 for( j = 0; j < cols; j++ )
977 mat[i*cols + j] = ((float*)(transmat->data.ptr + transmat->step*i))[j];
978 }
979 else
980 {
981 assert( mat_depth == CV_64F );
982 for( i = 0; i < transmat->rows; i++ )
983 for( j = 0; j < cols; j++ )
984 mat[i*cols + j] = ((double*)(transmat->data.ptr + transmat->step*i))[j];
985 }
986
987 // transform data
988 cols = a->cols * cn;
989 vector<double> buf(cols);
990
991 for( i = 0; i < a->rows; i++ )
992 {
993 uchar* src = a->data.ptr + i*a->step;
994 uchar* dst = b->data.ptr + i*b->step;
995
996 switch( depth )
997 {
998 case CV_32F:
999 for( j = 0; j < cols; j++ )
1000 buf[j] = ((float*)src)[j];
1001 break;
1002 case CV_64F:
1003 for( j = 0; j < cols; j++ )
1004 buf[j] = ((double*)src)[j];
1005 break;
1006 default:
1007 assert(0);
1008 }
1009
1010 switch( cn )
1011 {
1012 case 2:
1013 for( j = 0; j < cols; j += 2 )
1014 {
1015 double t0 = buf[j]*mat[0] + buf[j+1]*mat[1] + mat[2];
1016 double t1 = buf[j]*mat[3] + buf[j+1]*mat[4] + mat[5];
1017 double w = buf[j]*mat[6] + buf[j+1]*mat[7] + mat[8];
1018 w = w ? 1./w : 0;
1019 buf[j] = t0*w;
1020 buf[j+1] = t1*w;
1021 }
1022 break;
1023 case 3:
1024 for( j = 0; j < cols; j += 3 )
1025 {
1026 double t0 = buf[j]*mat[0] + buf[j+1]*mat[1] + buf[j+2]*mat[2] + mat[3];
1027 double t1 = buf[j]*mat[4] + buf[j+1]*mat[5] + buf[j+2]*mat[6] + mat[7];
1028 double t2 = buf[j]*mat[8] + buf[j+1]*mat[9] + buf[j+2]*mat[10] + mat[11];
1029 double w = buf[j]*mat[12] + buf[j+1]*mat[13] + buf[j+2]*mat[14] + mat[15];
1030 w = w ? 1./w : 0;
1031 buf[j] = t0*w;
1032 buf[j+1] = t1*w;
1033 buf[j+2] = t2*w;
1034 }
1035 break;
1036 default:
1037 assert(0);
1038 }
1039
1040 switch( depth )
1041 {
1042 case CV_32F:
1043 for( j = 0; j < cols; j++ )
1044 ((float*)dst)[j] = (float)buf[j];
1045 break;
1046 case CV_64F:
1047 for( j = 0; j < cols; j++ )
1048 ((double*)dst)[j] = buf[j];
1049 break;
1050 default:
1051 assert(0);
1052 }
1053 }
1054}
1055

1058{
1059 CvMat transmat = test_mat[INPUT][1];
1060 cvTsPerspectiveTransform( test_array[INPUT][0], test_array[REF_OUTPUT][0], &transmat );
1061}

1143 Core_CovarMatrixTest();

1146 int prepare_test_case( int test_case_idx );
1147 void run_func();
1148 void prepare_to_validation( int test_case_idx );
1149 vector<void*> temp_hdrs;
1150 vector<uchar> hdr_data;
1151 int flags, t_flag, len, count;
1152 bool are_images;
1153};
1154
1155
1156Core_CovarMatrixTest::Core_CovarMatrixTest() : Core_MatrixTest( 1, 1, true, false, 1 ),
1157flags(0), t_flag(0), are_images(false)
1158{
1159 test_case_count = 100;
1160 test_array[INPUT_OUTPUT].push_back(NULL);
1161 test_array[REF_INPUT_OUTPUT].push_back(NULL);
1162 test_array[TEMP].push_back(NULL);
1163 test_array[TEMP].push_back(NULL);

1165
1166
1167void Core_CovarMatrixTest::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( int test_case_idx, vector<vector<Size> >& sizes, vector<vector<int> >& types )
1168{
1169 RNG& rng = ts->get_rng();
1170 int bits = cvtest::randInt(rng);
1171 int i, single_matrix;
1172 Core_MatrixTest::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( test_case_idx, sizes, types );
1173
1174 flags = bits & (CV_COVAR_NORMAL | CV_COVAR_USE_AVG | CV_COVAR_SCALE | CV_COVAR_ROWS );
1175 single_matrix = flags & CV_COVAR_ROWS;
1176 t_flag = (bits & 256) != 0;
1177
1178 const int min_count = 2;
1179
1180 if( !t_flag )
1181 {
1182 len = sizes[INPUT][0].width;
1183 count = sizes[INPUT][0].height;
1184 count = MAX(count, min_count);
1185 sizes[INPUT][0] = Size(len, count);
1186 }
1187 else
1188 {
1189 len = sizes[INPUT][0].height;
1190 count = sizes[INPUT][0].width;
1191 count = MAX(count, min_count);
1192 sizes[INPUT][0] = Size(count, len);
1193 }
1194
1195 if( single_matrix && t_flag )
1196 flags = (flags & ~CV_COVAR_ROWS) | CV_COVAR_COLS;
1197
1198 if( CV_MAT_DEPTH(types[INPUT][0]) == CV_32S )
1199 types[INPUT][0] = (types[INPUT][0] & ~CV_MAT_DEPTH_MASK) | CV_32F;
1200
1201 sizes[OUTPUT][0] = sizes[REF_OUTPUT][0] = flags & CV_COVAR_NORMAL ? Size(len,len) : Size(count,count);
1202 sizes[INPUT_OUTPUT][0] = sizes[REF_INPUT_OUTPUT][0] = !t_flag ? Size(len,1) : Size(1,len);
1203 sizes[TEMP][0] = sizes[INPUT][0];
1204
1205 types[INPUT_OUTPUT][0] = types[REF_INPUT_OUTPUT][0] =
1206 types[OUTPUT][0] = types[REF_OUTPUT][0] = types[TEMP][0] =
1207 CV_MAT_DEPTH(types[INPUT][0]) == CV_64F || (bits & 512) ? CV_64F : CV_32F;
1208
1209 are_images = (bits & 1024) != 0;
1210 for( i = 0; i < (single_matrix ? 1 : count); i++ )
1211 temp_hdrs.push_back(NULL);
1212}
1213
1214
1215int Core_CovarMatrixTest::prepare_test_case( int test_case_idx )
1216{
1217 int code = Core_MatrixTest::prepare_test_case( test_case_idx );
1218 if( code > 0 )
1219 {
1220 int i;
1221 int single_matrix = flags & (CV_COVAR_ROWS|CV_COVAR_COLS);
1222 int hdr_size = are_images ? sizeof(IplImage) : sizeof(CvMat);
1223
1224 hdr_data.resize(count*hdr_size);
1225 uchar* _hdr_data = &hdr_data[0];
1226 if( single_matrix )
1227 {
1228 if( !are_images )
1229 *((CvMat*)_hdr_data) = test_mat[INPUT][0];
1230 else
1231 *((IplImage*)_hdr_data) = test_mat[INPUT][0];
1232 temp_hdrs[0] = _hdr_data;
1233 }
1234 else
1235 for( i = 0; i < count; i++ )
1236 {
1237 Mat part;
1238 void* ptr = _hdr_data + i*hdr_size;
1239
1240 if( !t_flag )
1241 part = test_mat[INPUT][0].row(i);
1242 else
1243 part = test_mat[INPUT][0].col(i);
1244
1245 if( !are_images )
1246 *((CvMat*)ptr) = part;
1247 else
1248 *((IplImage*)ptr) = part;
1249
1250 temp_hdrs[i] = ptr;
1251 }
1252 }
1253
1254 return code;
1255}

1259{
1260 cvCalcCovarMatrix( (const void**)&temp_hdrs[0], count,
1261 test_array[OUTPUT][0], test_array[INPUT_OUTPUT][0], flags );
1262}

1264
1265void Core_CovarMatrixTest::prepare_to_validation( int )
1266{
1267 Mat& avg = test_mat[REF_INPUT_OUTPUT][0];
1268 double scale = 1.;
1269
1270 if( !(flags & CV_COVAR_USE_AVG) )
1271 {
1272 Mat hdrs0 = cvarrToMat(temp_hdrs[0]);
1273
1274 int i;
1275 avg = Scalar::all(0);
1276
1277 for( i = 0; i < count; i++ )
1278 {
1279 Mat vec;
1280 if( flags & CV_COVAR_ROWS )
1281 vec = hdrs0.row(i);
1282 else if( flags & CV_COVAR_COLS )
1283 vec = hdrs0.col(i);
1284 else
1285 vec = cvarrToMat(temp_hdrs[i]);
1286
1287 cvtest::add(avg, 1, vec, 1, Scalar::all(0), avg, avg.type());
1288 }
1289
1290 cvtest::add(avg, 1./count, avg, 0., Scalar::all(0), avg, avg.type());
1291 }
1292
1293 if( flags & CV_COVAR_SCALE )
1294 {
1295 scale = 1./count;
1296 }
1297
1298 Mat& temp0 = test_mat[TEMP][0];
1299 cv::repeat( avg, temp0.rows/avg.rows, temp0.cols/avg.cols, temp0 );
1300 cvtest::add( test_mat[INPUT][0], 1, temp0, -1, Scalar::all(0), temp0, temp0.type());
1301
1302 cvtest::gemm( temp0, temp0, scale, Mat(), 0., test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0],
1303 t_flag ^ ((flags & CV_COVAR_NORMAL) != 0) ? CV_GEMM_A_T : CV_GEMM_B_T );
1304 temp_hdrs.clear();
1305}

1308static void cvTsFloodWithZeros( Mat& mat, RNG& rng )
1309{
1310 int k, total = mat.rows*mat.cols, type = mat.type();
1311 int zero_total = cvtest::randInt(rng) % total;
1312 CV_Assert( type == CV_32FC1 || type == CV_64FC1 );
1313
1314 for( k = 0; k < zero_total; k++ )
1315 {
1316 int i = cvtest::randInt(rng) % mat.rows;
1317 int j = cvtest::randInt(rng) % mat.cols;
1318
1319 if( type == CV_32FC1 )
1320 mat.at<float>(i,j) = 0.f;
1321 else
1322 mat.at<double>(i,j) = 0.;
1323 }
1324}

1391// LU method that chooses the optimal in a column pivot element
1392static double cvTsLU( CvMat* a, CvMat* b=NULL, CvMat* x=NULL, int* rank=0 )
1393{
1394 int i, j, k, N = a->rows, N1 = a->cols, Nm = MIN(N, N1), step = a->step/sizeof(double);
1395 int M = b ? b->cols : 0, b_step = b ? b->step/sizeof(double) : 0;
1396 int x_step = x ? x->step/sizeof(double) : 0;
1397 double *a0 = a->data.db, *b0 = b ? b->data.db : 0;
1398 double *x0 = x ? x->data.db : 0;
1399 double t, det = 1.;
1400 assert( CV_MAT_TYPE(a->type) == CV_64FC1 &&
1401 (!b || CV_ARE_TYPES_EQ(a,b)) && (!x || CV_ARE_TYPES_EQ(a,x)));
1402
1403 for( i = 0; i < Nm; i++ )
1404 {
1405 double max_val = fabs(a0[i*step + i]);
1406 double *a1, *a2, *b1 = 0, *b2 = 0;
1407 k = i;
1408
1409 for( j = i+1; j < N; j++ )
1410 {
1411 t = fabs(a0[j*step + i]);
1412 if( max_val < t )
1413 {
1414 max_val = t;
1415 k = j;
1416 }
1417 }
1418
1419 if( k != i )
1420 {
1421 for( j = i; j < N1; j++ )
1422 CV_SWAP( a0[i*step + j], a0[k*step + j], t );
1423
1424 for( j = 0; j < M; j++ )
1425 CV_SWAP( b0[i*b_step + j], b0[k*b_step + j], t );
1426 det = -det;
1427 }
1428
1429 if( max_val == 0 )
1430 {
1431 if( rank )
1432 *rank = i;
1433 return 0.;
1434 }
1435
1436 a1 = a0 + i*step;
1437 a2 = a1 + step;
1438 b1 = b0 + i*b_step;
1439 b2 = b1 + b_step;
1440
1441 for( j = i+1; j < N; j++, a2 += step, b2 += b_step )
1442 {
1443 t = a2[i]/a1[i];
1444 for( k = i+1; k < N1; k++ )
1445 a2[k] -= t*a1[k];
1446
1447 for( k = 0; k < M; k++ )
1448 b2[k] -= t*b1[k];
1449 }
1450
1451 det *= a1[i];
1452 }
1453
1454 if( x )
1455 {
1456 assert( b );
1457
1458 for( i = N-1; i >= 0; i-- )
1459 {
1460 double* a1 = a0 + i*step;
1461 double* b1 = b0 + i*b_step;
1462 for( j = 0; j < M; j++ )
1463 {
1464 t = b1[j];
1465 for( k = i+1; k < N1; k++ )
1466 t -= a1[k]*x0[k*x_step + j];
1467 x0[i*x_step + j] = t/a1[i];
1468 }
1469 }
1470 }
1471
1472 if( rank )
1473 *rank = i;
1474 return det;
1475}
1476

1481 CvMat temp0 = test_mat[TEMP][0];
1482 test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0].at<Scalar>(0,0) = cvRealScalar(cvTsLU(&temp0, 0, 0));

1585static double cvTsSVDet( CvMat* mat, double* ratio )
1586{
1587 int type = CV_MAT_TYPE(mat->type);
1588 int i, nm = MIN( mat->rows, mat->cols );
1589 CvMat* w = cvCreateMat( nm, 1, type );
1590 double det = 1.;
1591
1592 cvSVD( mat, w, 0, 0, 0 );
1593
1594 if( type == CV_32FC1 )
1595 {
1596 for( i = 0; i < nm; i++ )
1597 det *= w->data.fl[i];
1598 *ratio = w->data.fl[nm-1] < FLT_EPSILON ? 0 : w->data.fl[nm-1]/w->data.fl[0];
1599 }
1600 else
1601 {
1602 for( i = 0; i < nm; i++ )
1603 det *= w->data.db[i];
1604 *ratio = w->data.db[nm-1] < FLT_EPSILON ? 0 : w->data.db[nm-1]/w->data.db[0];
1605 }
1606
1607 cvReleaseMat( &w );
1608 return det;
1609}

1611void Core_InvertTest::prepare_to_validation( int )
1612{
1613 Mat& input = test_mat[INPUT][0];
1614 Mat& temp0 = test_mat[TEMP][0];
1615 Mat& temp1 = test_mat[TEMP][1];
1616 Mat& dst0 = test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0];
1617 Mat& dst = test_mat[OUTPUT][0];
1618 CvMat _input = input;
1619 double ratio = 0, det = cvTsSVDet( &_input, &ratio );
1620 double threshold = (input.depth() == CV_32F ? FLT_EPSILON : DBL_EPSILON)*1000;
1621
1622 cvtest::convert( input, temp1, temp1.type() );
1623
1624 if( det < threshold ||
1625 ((method == CV_LU || method == CV_CHOLESKY) && (result == 0 || ratio < threshold)) ||
1626 ((method == CV_SVD || method == CV_SVD_SYM) && result < threshold) )
1627 {
1628 dst = Scalar::all(0);
1629 dst0 = Scalar::all(0);
1630 return;
1631 }
1632
1633 if( input.rows >= input.cols )
1634 cvtest::gemm( temp0, input, 1., Mat(), 0., dst, 0 );
1635 else
1636 cvtest::gemm( input, temp0, 1., Mat(), 0., dst, 0 );
1637
1638 cv::setIdentity( dst0, Scalar::all(1) );
1639}

1741void Core_SolveTest::prepare_to_validation( int )
1742{
1743 //int rank = test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0].rows;

1759 }

1773
1774 cvtest::gemm( input, test_mat[TEMP][0], 1., test_mat[INPUT][1], -1., *pdst, 0 );

1812
1813void Core_SVDTest::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( int test_case_idx, vector<vector<Size> >& sizes, vector<vector<int> >& types )
1814{
1815 RNG& rng = ts->get_rng();
1816 int bits = cvtest::randInt(rng);
1817 Core_MatrixTest::get_test_array_types_and_sizes( test_case_idx, sizes, types );
1818 int min_size, i, m, n;
1819
1820 min_size = MIN( sizes[INPUT][0].width, sizes[INPUT][0].height );
1821
1822 flags = bits & (CV_SVD_MODIFY_A+CV_SVD_U_T+CV_SVD_V_T);
1823 have_u = (bits & 8) != 0;
1824 have_v = (bits & 16) != 0;
1825 symmetric = (bits & 32) != 0;
1826 compact = (bits & 64) != 0;
1827 vector_w = (bits & 128) != 0;
1828
1829 if( symmetric )
1830 sizes[INPUT][0] = Size(min_size, min_size);
1831
1832 m = sizes[INPUT][0].height;
1833 n = sizes[INPUT][0].width;
1834
1835 if( compact )
1836 sizes[TEMP][0] = Size(min_size, min_size);
1837 else
1838 sizes[TEMP][0] = sizes[INPUT][0];
1839 sizes[TEMP][3] = Size(0,0);
1840
1841 if( vector_w )
1842 {
1843 sizes[TEMP][3] = sizes[TEMP][0];
1844 if( bits & 256 )
1845 sizes[TEMP][0] = Size(1, min_size);
1846 else
1847 sizes[TEMP][0] = Size(min_size, 1);
1848 }
1849
1850 if( have_u )
1851 {
1852 sizes[TEMP][1] = compact ? Size(min_size, m) : Size(m, m);
1853
1854 if( flags & CV_SVD_U_T )
1855 CV_SWAP( sizes[TEMP][1].width, sizes[TEMP][1].height, i );
1856 }
1857 else
1858 sizes[TEMP][1] = Size(0,0);
1859
1860 if( have_v )
1861 {
1862 sizes[TEMP][2] = compact ? Size(n, min_size) : Size(n, n);
1863
1864 if( !(flags & CV_SVD_V_T) )
1865 CV_SWAP( sizes[TEMP][2].width, sizes[TEMP][2].height, i );
1866 }
1867 else
1868 sizes[TEMP][2] = Size(0,0);
1869
1870 types[TEMP][0] = types[TEMP][1] = types[TEMP][2] = types[TEMP][3] = types[INPUT][0];
1871 types[OUTPUT][0] = types[OUTPUT][1] = types[OUTPUT][2] = types[INPUT][0];
1872 types[OUTPUT][3] = CV_8UC1;
1873 sizes[OUTPUT][0] = !have_u || !have_v ? Size(0,0) : sizes[INPUT][0];
1874 sizes[OUTPUT][1] = !have_u ? Size(0,0) : compact ? Size(min_size,min_size) : Size(m,m);
1875 sizes[OUTPUT][2] = !have_v ? Size(0,0) : compact ? Size(min_size,min_size) : Size(n,n);
1876 sizes[OUTPUT][3] = Size(min_size,1);
1877
1878 for( i = 0; i < 4; i++ )
1879 {
1880 sizes[REF_OUTPUT][i] = sizes[OUTPUT][i];
1881 types[REF_OUTPUT][i] = types[OUTPUT][i];
1882 }
1883}

1886int Core_SVDTest::prepare_test_case( int test_case_idx )
1887{
1888 int code = Core_MatrixTest::prepare_test_case( test_case_idx );
1889 if( code > 0 )
1890 {
1891 Mat& input = test_mat[INPUT][0];
1892 cvTsFloodWithZeros( input, ts->get_rng() );
1893
1894 if( symmetric && (have_u || have_v) )
1895 {
1896 Mat& temp = test_mat[TEMP][have_u ? 1 : 2];
1897 cvtest::gemm( input, input, 1., Mat(), 0., temp, CV_GEMM_B_T );
1898 cvtest::copy( temp, input );
1899 }
1900
1901 if( (flags & CV_SVD_MODIFY_A) && test_array[OUTPUT][0] )
1902 cvtest::copy( input, test_mat[OUTPUT][0] );
1903 }
1904
1905 return code;
1906}

1932void Core_SVDTest::prepare_to_validation( int /*test_case_idx*/ )
1933{
1934 Mat& input = test_mat[INPUT][0];
1935 int depth = input.depth();
1936 int i, m = input.rows, n = input.cols, min_size = MIN(m, n);
1937 Mat *src, *dst, *w;
1938 double prev = 0, threshold = depth == CV_32F ? FLT_EPSILON : DBL_EPSILON;
1939
1940 if( have_u )
1941 {
1942 src = &test_mat[TEMP][1];
1943 dst = &test_mat[OUTPUT][1];
1944 cvtest::gemm( *src, *src, 1., Mat(), 0., *dst, src->rows == dst->rows ? CV_GEMM_B_T : CV_GEMM_A_T );
1945 cv::setIdentity( test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][1], Scalar::all(1.) );
1946 }
1947
1948 if( have_v )
1949 {
1950 src = &test_mat[TEMP][2];
1951 dst = &test_mat[OUTPUT][2];
1952 cvtest::gemm( *src, *src, 1., Mat(), 0., *dst, src->rows == dst->rows ? CV_GEMM_B_T : CV_GEMM_A_T );
1953 cv::setIdentity( test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][2], Scalar::all(1.) );
1954 }
1955
1956 w = &test_mat[TEMP][0];
1957 for( i = 0; i < min_size; i++ )
1958 {
1959 double normval = 0, aii;
1960 if( w->rows > 1 && w->cols > 1 )
1961 {
1962 normval = cvtest::norm( w->row(i), NORM_L1 );
1963 aii = depth == CV_32F ? w->at<float>(i,i) : w->at<double>(i,i);
1964 }
1965 else
1966 {
1967 normval = aii = depth == CV_32F ? w->at<float>(i) : w->at<double>(i);
1968 }
1969
1970 normval = fabs(normval - aii);
1971 test_mat[OUTPUT][3].at<uchar>(i) = aii >= 0 && normval < threshold && (i == 0 || aii <= prev);
1972 prev = aii;
1973 }
1974
1975 test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][3] = Scalar::all(1);
1976
1977 if( have_u && have_v )
1978 {
1979 if( vector_w )
1980 {
1981 test_mat[TEMP][3] = Scalar::all(0);
1982 for( i = 0; i < min_size; i++ )
1983 {
1984 double val = depth == CV_32F ? w->at<float>(i) : w->at<double>(i);
1985 cvSetReal2D( test_array[TEMP][3], i, i, val );
1986 }
1987 w = &test_mat[TEMP][3];
1988 }
1989
1990 if( m >= n )
1991 {
1992 cvtest::gemm( test_mat[TEMP][1], *w, 1., Mat(), 0., test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0],
1993 flags & CV_SVD_U_T ? CV_GEMM_A_T : 0 );
1994 cvtest::gemm( test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0], test_mat[TEMP][2], 1., Mat(), 0.,
1995 test_mat[OUTPUT][0], flags & CV_SVD_V_T ? 0 : CV_GEMM_B_T );
1996 }
1997 else
1998 {
1999 cvtest::gemm( *w, test_mat[TEMP][2], 1., Mat(), 0., test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0],
2000 flags & CV_SVD_V_T ? 0 : CV_GEMM_B_T );
2001 cvtest::gemm( test_mat[TEMP][1], test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0], 1., Mat(), 0.,
2002 test_mat[OUTPUT][0], flags & CV_SVD_U_T ? CV_GEMM_A_T : 0 );
2003 }
2004
2005 cvtest::copy( test_mat[INPUT][0], test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0] );
2006 }
2007}

2144void Core_SVBkSbTest::prepare_to_validation( int )
2145{
2146 Mat& input = test_mat[INPUT][0];
2147 int i, m = input.rows, n = input.cols, min_size = MIN(m, n);
2148 bool is_float = input.type() == CV_32F;
2149 Size w_size = compact ? Size(min_size,min_size) : Size(m,n);
2150 Mat& w = test_mat[TEMP][0];
2151 Mat wdb( w_size.height, w_size.width, CV_64FC1 );
2152 CvMat _w = w, _wdb = wdb;
2153 // use exactly the same threshold as in icvSVD... ,
2154 // so the changes in the library and here should be synchronized.
2155 double threshold = cv::sum(w)[0]*(DBL_EPSILON*2);//(is_float ? FLT_EPSILON*10 : DBL_EPSILON*2);
2156
2157 wdb = Scalar::all(0);
2158 for( i = 0; i < min_size; i++ )
2159 {
2160 double wii = vector_w ? cvGetReal1D(&_w,i) : cvGetReal2D(&_w,i,i);
2161 cvSetReal2D( &_wdb, i, i, wii > threshold ? 1./wii : 0. );
2162 }
2163
2164 Mat u = test_mat[TEMP][1];
2165 Mat v = test_mat[TEMP][2];
2166 Mat b = test_mat[INPUT][1];
2167
2168 if( is_float )
2169 {
2170 test_mat[TEMP][1].convertTo(u, CV_64F);
2171 test_mat[TEMP][2].convertTo(v, CV_64F);
2172 if( !b.empty() )
2173 test_mat[INPUT][1].convertTo(b, CV_64F);
2174 }
2175
2176 Mat t0, t1;
2177
2178 if( !b.empty() )
2179 cvtest::gemm( u, b, 1., Mat(), 0., t0, !(flags & CV_SVD_U_T) ? CV_GEMM_A_T : 0 );
2180 else if( flags & CV_SVD_U_T )
2181 cvtest::copy( u, t0 );
2182 else
2183 cvtest::transpose( u, t0 );
2184
2185 cvtest::gemm( wdb, t0, 1, Mat(), 0, t1, 0 );
2186
2187 cvtest::gemm( v, t1, 1, Mat(), 0, t0, flags & CV_SVD_V_T ? CV_GEMM_A_T : 0 );
2188 Mat& dst0 = test_mat[REF_OUTPUT][0];
2189 t0.convertTo(dst0, dst0.type() );
2190}

2193typedef std::complex<double> complex_type;
2194
2195struct pred_complex
2196{
2197 bool operator() (const complex_type& lhs, const complex_type& rhs) const
2198 {
2199 return fabs(lhs.real() - rhs.real()) > fabs(rhs.real())*FLT_EPSILON ? lhs.real() < rhs.real() : lhs.imag() < rhs.imag();
2200 }
2201};
2202
2203struct pred_double
2204{
2205 bool operator() (const double& lhs, const double& rhs) const
2206 {
2207 return lhs < rhs;
2208 }
2209};

2211class Core_SolvePolyTest : public cvtest::BaseTest
2212{
2213public:
2214 Core_SolvePolyTest();
2215 ~Core_SolvePolyTest();

2224void Core_SolvePolyTest::run( int )
2225{
2226 RNG& rng = ts->get_rng();
2227 int fig = 100;
2228 double range = 50;
2229 double err_eps = 1e-4;
2230
2231 for (int idx = 0, max_idx = 1000, progress = 0; idx < max_idx; ++idx)
2232 {
2233 progress = update_progress(progress, idx-1, max_idx, 0);
2234 int n = cvtest::randInt(rng) % 13 + 1;
2235 std::vector<complex_type> r(n), ar(n), c(n + 1, 0);
2236 std::vector<double> a(n + 1), u(n * 2), ar1(n), ar2(n);
2237
2238 int rr_odds = 3; // odds that we get a real root
2239 for (int j = 0; j < n;)
2240 {
2241 if (cvtest::randInt(rng) % rr_odds == 0 || j == n - 1)
2242 r[j++] = cvtest::randReal(rng) * range;
2243 else
2244 {
2245 r[j] = complex_type(cvtest::randReal(rng) * range,
2246 cvtest::randReal(rng) * range + 1);
2247 r[j + 1] = std::conj(r[j]);
2248 j += 2;
2249 }
2250 }
2251
2252 for (int j = 0, k = 1 << n, jj, kk; j < k; ++j)
2253 {
2254 int p = 0;
2255 complex_type v(1);
2256 for (jj = 0, kk = 1; jj < n && !(j & kk); ++jj, ++p, kk <<= 1)
2257 ;
2258 for (; jj < n; ++jj, kk <<= 1)
2259 {
2260 if (j & kk)
2261 v *= -r[jj];
2262 else
2263 ++p;
2264 }
2265 c[p] += v;
2266 }
2267
2268 bool pass = false;
2269 double div = 0, s = 0;
2270 int cubic_case = idx & 1;
2271 for (int maxiter = 100; !pass && maxiter < 10000; maxiter *= 2, cubic_case = (cubic_case + 1) % 2)
2272 {
2273 for (int j = 0; j < n + 1; ++j)
2274 a[j] = c[j].real();
2275
2276 CvMat amat, umat;
2277 cvInitMatHeader(&amat, n + 1, 1, CV_64FC1, &a[0]);
2278 cvInitMatHeader(&umat, n, 1, CV_64FC2, &u[0]);
2279 cvSolvePoly(&amat, &umat, maxiter, fig);
2280
2281 for (int j = 0; j < n; ++j)
2282 ar[j] = complex_type(u[j * 2], u[j * 2 + 1]);
2283
2284 std::sort(r.begin(), r.end(), pred_complex());
2285 std::sort(ar.begin(), ar.end(), pred_complex());
2286
2287 pass = true;
2288 if( n == 3 )
2289 {
2290 ar2.resize(n);
2291 cv::Mat _umat2(3, 1, CV_64F, &ar2[0]), umat2 = _umat2;
2292 cvFlip(&amat, &amat, 0);
2293 int nr2;
2294 if( cubic_case == 0 )
2295 nr2 = cv::solveCubic(cv::Mat(&amat),umat2);
2296 else
2297 nr2 = cv::solveCubic(cv::Mat_<float>(cv::Mat(&amat)), umat2);
2298 cvFlip(&amat, &amat, 0);
2299 if(nr2 > 0)
2300 std::sort(ar2.begin(), ar2.begin()+nr2, pred_double());
2301 ar2.resize(nr2);
2302
2303 int nr1 = 0;
2304 for(int j = 0; j < n; j++)
2305 if( fabs(r[j].imag()) < DBL_EPSILON )
2306 ar1[nr1++] = r[j].real();
2307
2308 pass = pass && nr1 == nr2;
2309 if( nr2 > 0 )
2310 {
2311 div = s = 0;
2312 for(int j = 0; j < nr1; j++)
2313 {
2314 s += fabs(ar1[j]);
2315 div += fabs(ar1[j] - ar2[j]);
2316 }
2317 div /= s;
2318 pass = pass && div < err_eps;
2319 }
2320 }
2321
2322 div = s = 0;
2323 for (int j = 0; j < n; ++j)
2324 {
2325 s += fabs(r[j].real()) + fabs(r[j].imag());
2326 div += sqrt(pow(r[j].real() - ar[j].real(), 2) + pow(r[j].imag() - ar[j].imag(), 2));
2327 }
2328 div /= s;
2329 pass = pass && div < err_eps;
2330 }
2331
2332 //test bug #5623 - solves equation x^3 = 0
2333 cv::Mat coeffs_5623(4, 1, CV_64FC1);
2334 cv::Mat r_5623(3, 1, CV_64FC2);
2335 coeffs_5623.at<double>(0) = 1;
2336 coeffs_5623.at<double>(1) = 0;
2337 coeffs_5623.at<double>(2) = 0;
2338 coeffs_5623.at<double>(3) = 0;
2339 double prec_5623 = cv::solveCubic(coeffs_5623, r_5623);
2340 pass = pass && r_5623.at<double>(0) == 0 && r_5623.at<double>(1) == 0 && r_5623.at<double>(2) == 0;
2341 pass = pass && prec_5623 == 1;
2342
2343 if (!pass)
2344 {
2345 ts->set_failed_test_info(cvtest::TS::FAIL_INVALID_OUTPUT);
2346 ts->printf( cvtest::TS::LOG, "too big diff = %g\n", div );
2347
2348 for (size_t j=0;j<ar2.size();++j)
2349 ts->printf( cvtest::TS::LOG, "ar2[%d]=%g\n", j, ar2[j]);
2350 ts->printf(cvtest::TS::LOG, "\n");
2351
2352 for (size_t j=0;j<r.size();++j)
2353 ts->printf( cvtest::TS::LOG, "r[%d]=(%g, %g)\n", j, r[j].real(), r[j].imag());
2354 ts->printf( cvtest::TS::LOG, "\n" );
2355 for (size_t j=0;j<ar.size();++j)
2356 ts->printf( cvtest::TS::LOG, "ar[%d]=(%g, %g)\n", j, ar[j].real(), ar[j].imag());
2357 break;
2358 }
2359 }

2362template<typename T>
2363static void checkRoot(Mat& r, T re, T im)
2364{
2365 for (int i = 0; i < r.cols*r.rows; i++)
2366 {
2367 Vec<T, 2> v = *(Vec<T, 2>*)r.ptr(i);
2368 if (fabs(re - v[0]) < 1e-6 && fabs(im - v[1]) < 1e-6)
2369 {
2370 v[0] = std::numeric_limits<T>::quiet_NaN();
2371 v[1] = std::numeric_limits<T>::quiet_NaN();
2372 return;
2373 }
2374 }
2375 GTEST_NONFATAL_FAILURE_("Can't find root") << "(" << re << ", " << im << ")";
2376}
2377TEST(Core_SolvePoly, regression_5599)
2378{
2379 // x^4 - x^2 = 0, roots: 1, -1, 0, 0
2380 cv::Mat coefs = (cv::Mat_<float>(1,5) << 0, 0, -1, 0, 1 );
2381 {
2382 cv::Mat r;
2383 double prec;
2384 prec = cv::solvePoly(coefs, r);
2385 EXPECT_LE(prec, 1e-6);
2386 EXPECT_EQ(4u, r.total());
2387 //std::cout << "Preciseness = " << prec << std::endl;
2388 //std::cout << "roots:\n" << r << "\n" << std::endl;
2389 ASSERT_EQ(CV_32FC2, r.type());
2390 checkRoot<float>(r, 1, 0);
2391 checkRoot<float>(r, -1, 0);
2392 checkRoot<float>(r, 0, 0);
2393 checkRoot<float>(r, 0, 0);
2394 }
2395 // x^2 - 2x + 1 = 0, roots: 1, 1
2396 coefs = (cv::Mat_<float>(1,3) << 1, -2, 1 );
2397 {
2398 cv::Mat r;
2399 double prec;
2400 prec = cv::solvePoly(coefs, r);
2401 EXPECT_LE(prec, 1e-6);
2402 EXPECT_EQ(2u, r.total());
2403 //std::cout << "Preciseness = " << prec << std::endl;
2404 //std::cout << "roots:\n" << r << "\n" << std::endl;
2405 ASSERT_EQ(CV_32FC2, r.type());
2406 checkRoot<float>(r, 1, 0);
2407 checkRoot<float>(r, 1, 0);
2408 }

2585class CV_KMeansSingularTest : public cvtest::BaseTest
2586{
2587public:
2588 CV_KMeansSingularTest() {}
2589 ~CV_KMeansSingularTest() {}
2590protected:
2591 void run(int inVariant)
2592 {
2593 int i, iter = 0, N = 0, N0 = 0, K = 0, dims = 0;
2594 Mat labels;
2595 try
2596 {
2597 RNG& rng = theRNG();
2598 const int MAX_DIM=5;
2599 int MAX_POINTS = 100, maxIter = 100;
2600 for( iter = 0; iter < maxIter; iter++ )
2601 {
2602 ts->update_context(this, iter, true);
2603 dims = rng.uniform(inVariant == MAT_1_N_CDIM ? 2 : 1, MAX_DIM+1);
2604 N = rng.uniform(1, MAX_POINTS+1);
2605 N0 = rng.uniform(1, MAX(N/10, 2));
2606 K = rng.uniform(1, N+1);
2607
2608 if (inVariant == VECTOR)
2609 {
2610 dims = 2;
2611
2612 std::vector<cv::Point2f> data0(N0);
2613 rng.fill(data0, RNG::UNIFORM, -1, 1);
2614
2615 std::vector<cv::Point2f> data(N);
2616 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
2617 data[i] = data0[rng.uniform(0, N0)];
2618
2619 kmeans(data, K, labels, TermCriteria(TermCriteria::MAX_ITER+TermCriteria::EPS, 30, 0),
2620 5, KMEANS_PP_CENTERS);
2621 }
2622 else
2623 {
2624 Mat data0(N0, dims, CV_32F);
2625 rng.fill(data0, RNG::UNIFORM, -1, 1);
2626
2627 Mat data;
2628
2629 switch (inVariant)
2630 {
2631 case MAT_N_DIM_C1:
2632 data.create(N, dims, CV_32F);
2633 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
2634 data0.row(rng.uniform(0, N0)).copyTo(data.row(i));
2635 break;
2636
2637 case MAT_N_1_CDIM:
2638 data.create(N, 1, CV_32FC(dims));
2639 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
2640 memcpy(data.ptr(i), data0.ptr(rng.uniform(0, N0)), dims * sizeof(float));
2641 break;
2642
2643 case MAT_1_N_CDIM:
2644 data.create(1, N, CV_32FC(dims));
2645 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
2646 memcpy(data.data + i * dims * sizeof(float), data0.ptr(rng.uniform(0, N0)), dims * sizeof(float));
2647 break;
2648
2649 case MAT_N_DIM_C1_NONCONT:
2650 data.create(N, dims + 5, CV_32F);
2651 data = data(Range(0, N), Range(0, dims));
2652 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
2653 data0.row(rng.uniform(0, N0)).copyTo(data.row(i));
2654 break;
2655
2656 case MAT_N_1_CDIM_NONCONT:
2657 data.create(N, 3, CV_32FC(dims));
2658 data = data.colRange(0, 1);
2659 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
2660 memcpy(data.ptr(i), data0.ptr(rng.uniform(0, N0)), dims * sizeof(float));
2661 break;
2662 }
2663
2664 kmeans(data, K, labels, TermCriteria(TermCriteria::MAX_ITER+TermCriteria::EPS, 30, 0),
2665 5, KMEANS_PP_CENTERS);
2666 }
2667
2668 Mat hist(K, 1, CV_32S, Scalar(0));
2669 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
2670 {
2671 int l = labels.at<int>(i);
2672 CV_Assert(0 <= l && l < K);
2673 hist.at<int>(l)++;
2674 }
2675 for( i = 0; i < K; i++ )
2676 CV_Assert( hist.at<int>(i) != 0 );
2677 }
2678 }
2679 catch(...)
2680 {
2681 ts->printf(cvtest::TS::LOG,
2682 "context: iteration=%d, N=%d, N0=%d, K=%d\n",
2683 iter, N, N0, K);
2684 std::cout << labels << std::endl;
2685 ts->set_failed_test_info(cvtest::TS::FAIL_MISMATCH);
2686 }
2687 }

2704TEST(CovariationMatrixVectorOfMat, accuracy)
2705{
2706 unsigned int col_problem_size = 8, row_problem_size = 8, vector_size = 16;
2707 cv::Mat src(vector_size, col_problem_size * row_problem_size, CV_32F);
2708 int singleMatFlags = CV_COVAR_ROWS;
2709
2710 cv::Mat gold;
2711 cv::Mat goldMean;
2712 cv::randu(src,cv::Scalar(-128), cv::Scalar(128));
2713 cv::calcCovarMatrix(src,gold,goldMean,singleMatFlags,CV_32F);
2714 std::vector<cv::Mat> srcVec;
2715 for(size_t i = 0; i < vector_size; i++)
2716 {
2717 srcVec.push_back(src.row(static_cast<int>(i)).reshape(0,col_problem_size));
2718 }
2719
2720 cv::Mat actual;
2721 cv::Mat actualMean;
2722 cv::calcCovarMatrix(srcVec, actual, actualMean,singleMatFlags,CV_32F);
2723
2724 cv::Mat diff;
2725 cv::absdiff(gold, actual, diff);
2726 cv::Scalar s = cv::sum(diff);
2727 ASSERT_EQ(s.dot(s), 0.0);
2728
2729 cv::Mat meanDiff;
2730 cv::absdiff(goldMean, actualMean.reshape(0,1), meanDiff);
2731 cv::Scalar sDiff = cv::sum(meanDiff);
2732 ASSERT_EQ(sDiff.dot(sDiff), 0.0);
2733}

2745 cv::reduce(src,goldMean,0 ,CV_REDUCE_AVG, CV_32F);
2746
2747 cv::calcCovarMatrix(src,gold,goldMean,singleMatFlags,CV_32F);
2748
2749 std::vector<cv::Mat> srcVec;
2750 for(size_t i = 0; i < vector_size; i++)

2752 srcVec.push_back(src.row(static_cast<int>(i)).reshape(0,col_problem_size));
2753 }
2754
2755 cv::Mat actual;
2756 cv::Mat actualMean = goldMean.reshape(0, row_problem_size);
2757 cv::calcCovarMatrix(srcVec, actual, actualMean,singleMatFlags,CV_32F);
2758
2759 cv::Mat diff;
